section.section:
Regulations under subsection (a) of this section shall include consideration of:
The establishment of land size limits for which cost-share assistance may be granted;
A determination of practices that are eligible for cost-sharing assistance;
Subject to the limitations imposed by this subtitle, the establishment of maximum amounts of assistance that an eligible landowner may receive for implementation of an approved practice;
The establishment of criteria for prioritizing applications, including size of land, soil productivity, and tree species;
A periodic review of actual costs of woodland development practices;
The establishment of criteria for Department assistance in implementation of an approved practice;
The imposition by the Department of reasonable charges for implementation assistance; and
A system of monitoring the implementation of approved practices.
